http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/A.-Ravindra-elected-chairman-of-ISEC-Board/article13992603.ece

The newly constituted Board of Governors of the Institute for Social and Economic Change (ISEC) has unanimously elected the former chief secretary of Karnataka, A. Ravindra, as its chairperson.He will have a tenure of three years.Dr. Ravindra has also served as Deputy Chairman of the Karnataka State Planning Board and Advisor to the Chief Minister of Karnataka.He is the founder-chairman of the Centre for Sustainable Development, a non-profit organisation.Dr. Ravindra, who holds a Ph.D. in development studies with specialisation in urban sector, has been a visiting faculty at Indian Institute of Management-Bengaluru.